@{
    ViewData["Title"] = "Privacy Policy";
}

<h1>@ViewData["Title"]</h1>

<p>
   
        <b>
             Privacy Policy..  <br>

        Welcome to the **Library Management System**.
    </b> <br>
        We are committed to protecting the privacy and security of our users. This Privacy Policy explains how information is collected, used, stored, and protected while using this application. 
            <br>
    <b>
        1. Information We Collect
    </b> <br>

            The Library Management System may collect the following information:<br>

    * Full Name
    * Student or Member ID
    * Email Address
    * Phone Number (if applicable)
    * User Account Credentials
    * Book Borrowing and Return History
    * Fine and Payment Records (if applicable)
    * Login Activity and System Logs <br>

    
    <b> 2. Purpose of Data Collection </b>
    <br>

            The collected information is used to:<br>

    * Manage library memberships.
    * Maintain accurate book inventory records.
    * Process book issue, renewal, and return transactions.
    * Track overdue books and applicable fines.
    * Authenticate users and provide secure access.
    * Generate administrative reports and analytics.
    * Improve the efficiency and reliability of library services. <br>

        <b>
        3. Data Security
    </b>
    <br>

            We implement appropriate technical and organizational measures to safeguard user information against unauthorized access, disclosure, modification, or loss. Access to sensitive information is restricted to authorized personnel only.<br>

            <b>
        4. Data Retention
    </b> <br>

        User information is retained only for as long as necessary to provide library services, comply with institutional requirements, and maintain historical transaction records where applicable. <br>

                <b>
        5. Information Sharing
    </b><br>

    The Library Management System does not sell, rent, or distribute personal information to third parties. Information may only be shared when required by law or with authorized institutional administrators for library management purposes. <br>

                    <b>
        6. User Responsibilities
    </b> <br>

            Users are responsible for: <br>

    * Providing accurate and up-to-date information.
    * Maintaining the confidentiality of their login credentials.
    * Reporting any unauthorized access to their account immediately.
        * Complying with all library policies and regulations. <br>

                        <b>
        7. Cookies and Session Data
    </b> <br>

        This application may use session cookies or temporary authentication tokens to maintain secure user sessions. These are used solely for system functionality and security purposes. <br>

                            <b>
        8. Changes to This Privacy Policy
    </b> <br>

        This Privacy Policy may be updated periodically to reflect changes in system functionality, legal requirements, or institutional policies. Continued use of the application constitutes acceptance of the updated policy.<br>

                                <b>
        9. Contact Information
    </b><br>

            For questions regarding this Privacy Policy or the handling of personal information, please contact the Library Administrator. <br>

